requent, and generally represent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Maredudd Fychan ap TEGWARED was born in Caernarfonshire, Wales as the son of Tegwared ap HYWEL and Mrs. Tegwared ap Hywel. He had at least 1 son with Gwenllian ferch Hywel."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1338–Male":"1338–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1288–Female":"1288–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1400–1440":"1400–1440","1312–Male":"1312–Surnud","1316–Female":"1316–Surnud","1316":"1316","1338":"1338","1312":"1312","1400":"1400","1288":"1288","about 1400":"umbes 1400","1440":"1440","Dolbenmaen, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Dolbenmaen, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1338–Male":"1338–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1288–Female":"1288–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1400–1440":"1400–1440","1312–Male":"1312–Kuollut","1316–Female":"1316–Kuollut","1316":"1316","1338":"1338","1312":"1312","1400":"1400","1288":"1288","about 1400":"noin 1400","1440":"1440","Dolbenmaen, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Dolbenmaen, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","1338–Male":"1338–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1288–Female":"1288–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1400–1440":"1400–1440","1312–Male":"1312–Décédé","1316–Fe